.TH "__tty_insert_flip_char" 9 "__tty_insert_flip_char" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__tty_insert_flip_char \- Add one character to the tty buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __tty_insert_flip_char
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ","
.BI "unsigned char ch "  ","
.BI "char flag "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty port
.IP "ch" 12
character
.IP "flag" 12
flag byte

Queue a single byte to the tty buffering, with an optional flag.
This is the slow path of tty_insert_flip_char.
